This question already has answers here : How do I simplify and evaluate the limit of $(\sqrt x - 1)/(\sqrt[3] x - 1)$ as $x\to 1$? (7 answers) Evaluating $\lim _{x\to 1}\left(\frac{\sqrt[3]{x}-1}{2\sqrt{x}-2}\right)$ [duplicate] (6 answers) Closed 8 years ago . $$
\lim_{x\to 1} \frac{ \sqrt{x} - 1}{\sqrt[3]{x} - 1}
$$ I multiply it with: $$
\frac{ \sqrt{x} + 1}{\sqrt{x} + 1}
$$ And I get : $$
\lim_{x\to 1} \frac{ \sqrt{x}^2 - 1^2}{(\sqrt[3]{x} - 1) * (\sqrt{x} + 1)}
$$ But the solution is still division by 0 and not possible, so I think I've made a mistake somewhere..
